<br>
I take it you never played Anarchy Online.  This is a direct steal.  Frankly, it isn't nearly as much fun.  Here is why....<br>
<br>
Halfway through the dungeon crawl &quot;Sorry guys, I gotta go, can someone port me out&quot;.  Now there is no way of shouting to the zone &quot;group of 5 looking for 1 more&quot;.  There is no way because no one else is IN the zone, nor can they GET in the zone.  It's just you and your group.  <br>
<br>
While I wasn't fond of the lists we had to wait on pre-Kunark, and even less fond of keeping them &quot;Well, I have 3 healers ahead of you but I'll send you a tell&quot;, the ability for a group to be flexible as it play and for players to replace one another is part of what makes EQ work.  <br>
<br>
This was my least favorite feature of AO. <br>
